<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4d15a9dc-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12575"><num value="12575">§ 12575.</num><heading> Eligibility</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id4d15a9dd-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12575/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Scholarships</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A person shall be eligible to receive a scholarship under this part if the person has been employed in law enforcement for the 2-year period immediately preceding the date on which assistance is sought.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id4d15a9de-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12575/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Ineligibility for student employment</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A person who has been employed as a law enforcement officer is ineligible to participate in a student employment program carried out under this part.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id4d15a9df-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tXX/s200206">Pub. L. 103–322, title XX, § 200206</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/2059">108 Stat. 2059</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4d15a9e0-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">
